After Morendil's quite sweeping protos I've tried to come up with a
smaller solution. Check it out.

This is a first sketch of how Agora could interact with things
happening in MOOs, MUDs, etc with Agorans involved. It puts some
emphasis on building rather than just "playing" the MOO to avoid
stalemate when you've been walking and talking enough.

Yes, it's just a very moderate start.

But it could be extended. The contests statutes could require members
to pay Ergs to the contest for each MOO object they create. Agora
rules could force all Agorans involved with MOOs to become members in
this contest. And so on. The proto at the end of this mail is a simple
example of how the Agora rules could interact with such a contest, and
thus (indirectly) with the MOO. There is also the interesting question
of interacting with technical RL matters (e.g. who does Morendil grant
building rights to?).

This is kinda like minimalist nomic, with one gimmick (the
competitions) alrady thrown in. The rest could be developed from
within the contest.

I think that most of the things we wanted to realize in connection to
MOOs (short of a full move of Agora to a game within some MOO) could
be done on this basis. On the other hand, they could grow organically
from this small start, and there is very little risk involved, neither
of technical or MOO coding problems, nor of drawbacks for Agorans who
are unable or unwilling to move to a M** (except that they lose a
chance to generate some extra income - but note that the only net VT
input to the economy caused by this is through the subsidy).

What do you think? Would you enter such a contest? Vote in competition
surveys? Vote for the proto?

Kolja A.

__________
MOO builders' contest statutes (draft 1.0, 7.8.98)


1. Contestmaster

The first contestmaster is Kolja.

2. Motions

The statutes are changed by adopted motions. A motion is distributed
when a member of the contest sends it to all other members. It is up
for vote for seven days after its distribution. It takes effect when
the contestmaster publishes the voting results to all members after
these seven days, and if the necessary majority of votes cast for the
motion by members of the contest in mails to the contestmaster is
sufficient.

3. Majorities

Motions concerning single digit statutes need a two-thirds majority of
all votes cast to be adopted, others need a simple majority of all
votes cast.

4. Members 

Only players of Agora can become members of this contest. They may
become members by notifying the Contestmaster and paying the Entry Fee
to the contest.


10. Entry and Membership Fees

The Entry Fee for this Contest is 2 VTs.

The Membership Fee, to be paid by each member as soon as possible
after the first day of each month, is 1 VT.


20. The Competition

Every month, this contest organizes a MOO building competition.

It is held in two categories: Best Room and Best Object.

21. Submissions

During the whole month, all Agora players (not just contest members)
may nominate objects of any officially recognized MUD, MOO
etc. created by any member of the contest as entries to the
appropriate category of the competition.

22. Survey

As soon as possible after the first day of each month, the
Contestmaster shall post a complete list of competition submissions
made in the last month to the PF.

For two weeks after this distribution all players of Agora (not just
contest members) may cast one vote in each category of the
competition by notifying the Contestmaster. Members of the contest may
not vote for MOO objects they created themselves.

[Comment: Should we use the Referendum structure given in the rules,
or just a simple homemade survey as described here?]

As soon as possible after the end of this survey period the
Contestmaster shall publish all votes cast in the competition.

23. Rewards

Together with the publication of the survey results, the contestmaster
shall pay out the competition rewards. 

The reward for the winner of each competition category shall be a
fraction of 1/(n+2) of the contest's currency holdings (fractions
rounded down), where n is the number of categories.

[Comment: this assures the contest always has some money left to pay
taxes etc.]

In case of a tied win in a category, the reward shall be divided
evenly among the winners.

24. No rewards for bad debtors

If the winner of a category still owes the contest any currency at the
time e is to receive the reward, and at least one of these debts is
older than two weeks, the reward for this winner shall be cancelled.

25. Officially recognized M**s

AgoraMOO (netdive.com:7777) is an officially recognized MOO.

[Shattered world could be added here, as could LambdaMOO and any
other.] 

---------
Proto: Contest subsidies

[Comment: I've tried to phrase this such that the subsidy concept can
be generalized to other contests, too.]

As the development of a community of MOOing Agorans is welcomed by
Agora, be it hereby resolved to create a new rule with the title
"Contest subsidies" and the text:

As soon as possible after the end of each month the chancellor shall
pay out to each contest the monthly subsidy listed in this rule (if it
is nonzero).

The monthly subsidy for the MOO builders' contest is 2 VTs.

The monthly subsidy for all other contests is currently zero.

[Add your contest here if it gets your support for this proposal... ;)]

